stex - simple text editor
=========================
stex is an extremely fast and small text editor for Linux and UNIX


Requirements
------------
None for now.


Installation
------------
Edit config.mk to match your local setup (stex is installed into
the /usr/local namespace by default.)

Afterwards enter the following command to build and install stex (if
necessary as root):

    make clean install


Running stex
------------
Run stex via any terminal.

control + q to quit.

Configuration
-------------
The configuration of stex is done by creating a custom config.h
and (re)compiling the source code.
